BOARD
  Board and capture another ship.

SYNTAX
  board <victim-ship#> <boarder-ship#> [mil]
  boar  <victim-ship#> <boarder-ship#> [mil]

DESCRIPTION
  Sends military from one of your ships to board and capture another
  ship in the same sector. [mil] is how many troops to commit
  (default: all military aboard the boarder).

  If the victim has NO military aboard, it is captured automatically
  with no fight at all — zero defender strength always means an
  instant, casualty-free capture. This is the headline mechanic: an
  empty ship (crew all lost to earlier combat, or just never
  garrisoned) is always free for the taking.

  If the victim DOES have military aboard, it's a real fight, same
  strength math as 'attack':
    Attacker strength = boarding mil x your tech factor x boarder's efficiency
    Defender strength = victim's mil  x its tech factor  x victim's efficiency
  Casualties are taken on both sides regardless of outcome. On victory,
  the victim's remaining defenders are wiped, ownership transfers to
  you, and a single mil moves aboard as a token prize crew (the rest of
  your boarding party stays on your ship). On defeat, both sides just
  take losses — no ownership change.

  Requirements:
    - You must own the boarder ship (deity exempt)
    - Both ships must be in the same sector
    - You must be at war with the victim's owner, unless it's unowned
      (deity is exempt from the war requirement)

KNOWN GAPS (v1)
----------------
  4.4.1's real boar.c also lets you launch a boarding party from a
  sector's own militia or land units, not just from another ship, with
  a mobility-gated "approach" phase where nearby hostile coastal
  defense can fire back before the fight — not ported here, same scope
  cut already made for 'attack'/'assault''s approach-phase mechanics.
  Combat is a single round with proportional random casualties (same
  simplification 'attack' already uses), not the reference's granular
  one-casualty-at-a-time loop with recalculated odds.

EXAMPLE
  board 12 5           board ship #12 using all mil aboard ship #5
  board 12 5 20         board ship #12 using 20 mil from ship #5

